
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `mousetweaks` baraye tagheer daadane raftaare mouse dar GNOME desktop estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta settings mouse ra, mesle click-e khodkaar (automatic click) va highlight kardan pointer mouse, moratab konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--enable click-delay`  --> 🖱️ Fa'al kardane click-e khodkaar ba ta'khir.
    🔹 `--enable locate-pointer`  --> 📍 Fa'al kardane highlight kardan pointer mouse ba Ctrl.
    🔹 `--disable all`  --> 🚫 Gheyre fa'al kardane hameye tweak-ha.
    🔹 `--help` --> ℹ️ Namayesh rahnama va gozine-haye bishtar.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ mousetweaks --enable click-delay

    🔹 Fa'al kardane click-e khodkaar ba ta'khir.

    $ mousetweaks --enable locate-pointer

    🔹 Fa'al kardane highlight kardan pointer ba Ctrl.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ mousetweaks --enable click-delay --locate-pointer

    🔹 Fa'al kardane har do tweak click-e khodkaar va highlight kardan pointer ba Ctrl dar yek command.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `mousetweaks` command is used to modify mouse behavior in the GNOME desktop environment. It helps you configure mouse settings like automatic clicks and highlighting the mouse pointer.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--enable click-delay`  --> 🖱️ Enables automatic clicks with a delay.
    🔹 `--enable locate-pointer`  --> 📍 Enables highlighting the mouse pointer when Ctrl is pressed.
    🔹 `--disable all`  --> 🚫 Disables all tweaks.
    🔹 `--help` --> ℹ️ Displays help and more options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ mousetweaks --enable click-delay

    🔹 Enables automatic clicks with a delay.

    $ mousetweaks --enable locate-pointer

    🔹 Enables highlighting the pointer when Ctrl is pressed.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ mousetweaks --enable click-delay --locate-pointer

    🔹 Enables both automatic click and pointer highlighting tweaks in a single command.

